      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "FALSE TESTIMONY.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The law of retaliation is sternly laid down here; but it must be administered by the judges, not by men acting on their own behalf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(17) Both the men . . . shall stand before the Lord, before the priests and the judges.—This appears to mean that all cases of suspected false testimony were to go before the supreme court (see Deuteronomy 17:9); that the matter was not to be lightly decided.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(17) ",
            "children": []
