        "text": "If a false witness rise up — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A single witness, though he speak truth, is not to be accepted for the condemnation of another man; but if he be convicted of bearing false witness, it is sufficient for his own condemnation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Both the men shall stand before the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, shall come to the supreme court, which consisted partly of priests, and partly of other great persons, who, it seems, in Moses’s time, sat at the door of the tabernacle, and so the men, in standing before them, might properly be said to ",
        "children": []
